OL,3,CInside Port Talbot's steelworks as
OL,4,Cblast furnace era draws to a close
OL,6,FWe watch the cauldron ablaze, as the
OL,7,Firon is made into steel. The light
OL,8,Ffrom the molten metal floods the dark
OL,9,Ffurnace with an orange glow. The heat
OL,10,Ffrom this process of Basic Oxygen
OL,11,FSteelmaking is intense as temperatures
OL,12,Fcan reach 1,700C.
OL,14,FIt is like a vision of Dante's
OL,15,FInferno, but perhaps the best
OL,16,Fdescription is from the workers
OL,17,Fthemselves, who refer to this part of
OL,18,Fthe plant as the Eye of Sauron from
OL,19,FLord Of The Rings.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G9/12
