OL,3,CInside Port Talbot's steelworks as
OL,4,Cblast furnace era draws to a close
OL,6,FIf your job, or even your identity, is
OL,7,Fthe price of that change, though, it
OL,8,Fcan be very hard to accept, especially
OL,9,Ffor younger workers with families and
OL,10,Fmortgages, or older workers who
OL,11,Fhaven't known anything else.
OL,13,FI ask Graham how he will move on.
OL,15,FHe says he is planning to retire to
OL,16,FSpain for the warmer weather and a
OL,17,Ffresh start.
OL,19,FAs we chat, a loud rumble clatters
OL,20,Fabove our heads. Without missing a
OL,21,Fbeat, Graham recognises it instantly.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G11/12
